## Example environment variables (DO NOT put real secrets here)

## Domain allowlist (server-side)
# Regex used to validate email domains
ALLOWED_DOMAINS_REGEXP="@(example\.org|univ-lehavre\.fr)"

## App URL (public)
# Used when generating login/magic URL redirects
PUBLIC_LOGIN_URL="http://localhost:5173"

## Appwrite configuration
PUBLIC_APPWRITE_ENDPOINT="https://cloud.example.com/v1"
PUBLIC_APPWRITE_PROJECT="<appwrite_project_id>"
# Server-side API key (secret)
APPWRITE_KEY="<appwrite_api_key>"

## REDCap configuration
PUBLIC_REDCAP_URL="https://redcap.example.com/api/"
# Server-side token (secret)
REDCAP_API_TOKEN="<redcap_api_token>"

## Legal links shown in the UI
# RGPD information notice linked from the "Create request" modal.
# Per-environment because the survey id/token differs between prod
# and pre-prod instances.
PUBLIC_RGPD_NOTICE_URL="https://survey.example.com/surveys/?__file=<token>"
